data.title: Disney is reviving High School Musical with a whole new cast
data.meta_description: There's going to be a fourth High School Musical TV film with a new cast, according to Disney.
data.text:
The Disney Channel is reviving High School Musical.

The company says it's starting a nationwide casting search in America for the latest sequel in the TV film franchise.

Disney says High School Musical 4 will introduce new East High Wildcats and their cross-town rivals, the West High Knights.

The cast of the original 2006 movie included Zac Efron, Vanessa Hudgens, Ashley Tisdale and Corbin Bleu.

US television networks are increasingly focussing on musicals, with projects ranging from NBC's The Sound of Music to Fox's Grease, which starred Vanessa Hudgens.

Details about upcoming open casting calls will be available online soon on the Disney website, external - if you can afford the flight to the US.

Anne Hudgens, Monique Coleman and Ashley Tisdale

A broadcast date for High School Musical 4 hasn't been announced yet.

The first film was followed by two sequels - the first in 2007 and then High School Musical 3: Senior Year in 2008 - which starred British actress Jemma McKenzie-Brown as new character, Tiara Gold.

Jeffrey Hornaday, who directed the Disney Channel's Teen Beach Movie and Teen Beach 2, will direct and choreograph the new film.

Peter Barsocchini returns to High School Musical to write the script with Dan Berendsen.

Disney had announced a fourth film, external back in 2009 but it never materialised.

The original cast got back together for a 10-year anniversary reunion in January.

Vanessa Hudgens, Ashley Tisdale, Lucas Grabeel, Corbin Bleu and Monique Coleman were filmed for the special, which will air in the UK in September.

Zac Efron couldn't take part but sent a pre-recorded message for the documentary.

It'll show the cast members reminiscing about their time filming and how their careers have progressed since they left in 2008.

Vanessa Hudgens tweeted: It happened!! A little HSM reunion... 10 years later. Crazy!!! #hsmreunion, external

Vanessa Hudgens said: "It is so surreal being here. It's so crazy to me that 10 years has gone by and I see this cast and feel like it was yesterday.

"I still love them so much from the bottom of my heart."

Ashley Tisdale tweeted: Oh the feels....... Get ready because we're back celebrating 10th anniversary #wildcats #hsm , external

Ashley Tisdale said: "It was the fans who made this whole thing happen. They caught onto it and then it just started to grow."
